<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: When your job hinges on how well you talk to people, you learn a lot about how to have conversations -- and that most of us don&#39;t converse very well. Celeste Headlee has worked as a radio host for decades, and she knows the ingredients of a great conversation: Honesty, brevity, clarity and a healthy amount of listening. In this insightful talk, she shares 10 useful rules for having better conversations. &quot;Go out, talk to people, listen to people,&quot; she says. &quot;And, most importantly, be prepared to be amazed.&quot;" name="description" />
